1
00:00:06,005 --> 00:00:07,966
{\an8}TONPU MARKET STREET

2
00:00:16,391 --> 00:00:17,809
<i>Ouch.</i>

3
00:00:19,644 --> 00:00:23,898
To accept someone,
you have to face them first.

4
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:26,359
You're a guy who can do that,

5
00:00:26,443 --> 00:00:29,154
and it looks to me that
you want to accept others.

6
00:00:32,365 --> 00:00:34,701
Sheesh, just what does he see in me?

7
00:00:34,784 --> 00:00:37,037
-Good morning, Sakura-san
-Morning, Sakura-kun.

8
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:44,586
What are you guys?
When did you get behind me?

9
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:46,921
Suo-san and I have been
calling you for a while.

10
00:00:47,005 --> 00:00:48,590
Are you thinking about something?

11
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:51,092
What's that grin for?

12
00:00:51,176 --> 00:00:54,387
Huh? But you're the one
who was grinning, Sakura-kun.

13
00:00:54,471 --> 00:00:55,680
It was fun to watch.

14
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:59,476
I wasn't grinning!

15
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:01,311
FURIN HIGH SCHOOL

16
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,606
Oh, come on, Sakura-kun.

17
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:07,150
There's no need to be so embarrassed.

18
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:09,194
Shut up. Leave me alone.

19
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:14,491
It seems to me like
everyone's staring at us.

20
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:16,284
Well, you know why...

21
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:18,870
{\an8}Who cares? Not like
you're gonna die just from that.

22
00:01:18,953 --> 00:01:21,247
You should learn
to get used to it a little.

23
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:22,290
Oh, they are here!

24
00:01:22,373 --> 00:01:23,500
-Finally!
-They're here!

25
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:25,835
There are rumors
flying around about you guys!

26
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,837
You duked it out with Shishitoren!

27
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:29,339
So how'd it go?

28
00:01:29,422 --> 00:01:30,715
Give us all the details!

29
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:33,092
Wow, we got surrounded for interview!

30
00:01:33,176 --> 00:01:37,514
I see. So that's what the others
in the hallway wanted from us.

31
00:01:37,597 --> 00:01:38,973
Ask them!

32
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:45,021
-I'm counting on you, Nirei-kun!
-What?

33
00:01:47,065 --> 00:01:49,651
-You were in the fight, too?
-But your face looks fine.

34
00:01:49,734 --> 00:01:50,985
Who are you again?

35
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:56,825
My name is Akihiko Nirei!
Allow me to explain everything!

36
00:01:56,908 --> 00:01:59,160
Hey, hold it there.

37
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:02,080
Let me in on the fun, too.

38
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:10,213
Banana really is
the best flavor for protein.

39
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:14,342
Tsu... Tsuge...

40
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:17,637
<i>The guy who was doing pull-ups
the day before yesterday?</i>

41
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,890
Yes! He may seem a little eccentric,

42
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:24,686
but he should be just as strong as
Sugishita-san and Suo-san!

43
00:02:28,106 --> 00:02:31,025
Yo, it's been a while, Suo.

44
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:33,278
You finally wanna give me your answer?

45
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:36,865
I told you I don't want to, remember?

46
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:39,993
You both know each other, Suo-san?

47
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:41,703
Yeah, sort of.

48
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,455
Fine, then. Now it's about Sakura-kun.

49
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:47,667
Let me ask you a question.

50
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:50,336
What is your virtue?

51
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,254
BUFF

52
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:54,340
There it is! A live "What is your virtue?"

53
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:55,675
I knew he'd ask that.

54
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:58,136
He asked all of us that yesterday, too.

55
00:02:58,219 --> 00:03:00,138
Per... due?

56
00:03:00,221 --> 00:03:02,599
Not "perdue"! I said virtue!

57
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:04,475
Things you're particular about!

58
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:06,686
I wanted to ask you
the day before yesterday,

59
00:03:06,769 --> 00:03:08,438
but I wasn't done with my pull-ups.

60
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:12,150
But, hey, why are you even asking that?

61
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:13,985
What do you mean by "why"?

62
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:16,446
<i>One's virtue is
the principle of one's life!</i>

63
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:18,948
No harm in asking other people this!

64
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:20,992
-Oh, I get it!
-You do?

65
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:23,870
How someone embodies
their way of thinking shows

66
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:26,331
more of that person's nature
than just some data.

67
00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:31,753
You put your right shoe first and drink
SACAS brand protein, right, Tsugeura-san?

68
00:03:31,836 --> 00:03:33,713
Whoa! How did you know that?

69
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:35,340
CONFIDENTIAL

70
00:03:35,423 --> 00:03:36,507
Oh, that notebook.

71
00:03:36,591 --> 00:03:39,427
Unlike your figure, you seem to
have some sturdy virtue!

72
00:03:39,510 --> 00:03:41,137
Nah, it's not that big of a deal!

73
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:42,972
You don't have to be so modest here!

74
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,682
What is that guy's deal?

75
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:46,476
They're getting along well...

76
00:03:46,559 --> 00:03:49,604
Still, he's so hot-blooded
and such a pain.

77
00:03:49,687 --> 00:03:52,023
Is he really strong?

78
00:03:52,106 --> 00:03:53,066
Oh, yeah.

79
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:54,651
He's strong.

80
00:03:56,611 --> 00:04:00,531
Oh, I know! You guys want to hear
Sakura-kun's story, right?

81
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:02,909
Then how about we get together
after school

82
00:04:02,992 --> 00:04:05,828
and discuss our virtue over some food?

83
00:04:07,330 --> 00:04:09,916
Granny asked me to
get rid of the weeds today.

84
00:04:09,999 --> 00:04:12,752
-I gotta visit the dentist.
-My girlfriend's birthday...

85
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:15,755
What's this? You're all real busy, huh?

86
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:17,257
Looks like it.

87
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:18,549
Are they stupid?

88
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:20,677
They're both so optimistic.

89
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:26,015
Oh, Sugishita!
You got here at just the right time!

90
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:30,103
What? You're busy, too?

91
00:04:30,186 --> 00:04:32,605
No, I think his case
is a little different...

92
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:35,441
Then how about just the four of us?

93
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:37,986
I'll take you guys to
my favorite restaurant.

94
00:04:38,069 --> 00:04:39,028
Okay!

95
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:40,780
No, I'm not going.

96
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:41,823
Me neither.

97
00:04:41,906 --> 00:04:45,702
What? But Sakura-san,
there might be some delicious food there!

98
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:49,831
Looks like you're just as silly
as them, Sakura-kun.

99
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:51,582
Shut up!

100
00:06:28,888 --> 00:06:31,015
You can be quite forceful, huh, Nirei-kun?

101
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:34,352
So this is your favorite restaurant,
Tsugeura-san?

102
00:06:35,019 --> 00:06:36,479
Hey! Over here!

103
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:39,690
Can I really get good food here?

104
00:06:41,025 --> 00:06:42,068
{\an8}Well...

105
00:06:42,151 --> 00:06:43,820
{\an8}You hungry, Sakura-kun?

106
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:47,031
{\an8}I recommend the protein okonomiyaki!

107
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:51,327
{\an8}It doesn't use flour, high in protein and
low in sugar, making it good for muscles!

108
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:52,995
Oh! So healthy!

109
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:55,832
It looks pretty good in the picture.

110
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:57,917
Sakura-kun, you're so simple. How nice.

111
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,001
I'll just have water.

112
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:01,420
Do you like eating, Sakura-kun?

113
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:04,215
If you're particular about it,
that's a virtue too.

114
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,759
I'm not particular about it or anythin'.

115
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:09,053
You sure love having secrets.

116
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:11,472
Oh, well. If that's how you roll...

117
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:13,766
Let's fight.

118
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:16,227
Huh?

119
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:19,939
You were really cool when you said
you'd take the top two days ago.

120
00:07:20,022 --> 00:07:24,902
{\an8}Ain't no way someone who'd say that
in front of everyone has no virtue.

121
00:07:25,486 --> 00:07:28,531
{\an8}Not wanting to say it is also a virtue,

122
00:07:28,614 --> 00:07:32,410
{\an8}but I'll have you tell me with your fists!

123
00:07:33,744 --> 00:07:36,372
Fighting is a type of communication,
Sakura-kun.

124
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:40,334
Interesting.

125
00:07:47,383 --> 00:07:49,552
Oh, wow!

126
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:52,221
We came into quite a shop, huh?

127
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:53,931
But, well, maybe here we can...

128
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:55,308
Oh?

129
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:56,684
<i>That guy...</i>

130
00:07:58,644 --> 00:08:01,397
Hey, there! What a coincidence!

131
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:07,278
'Sup, Kiryu-kun!

132
00:08:07,361 --> 00:08:08,488
Wanna join us?

133
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:09,614
See you later.

134
00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:13,034
-Let's sit further inside.
-Oh, how cold.

135
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:16,746
-It's Kiryu-san!
-Oh, he's the one you're interested in?

136
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:18,122
Here you go.

137
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:20,416
Thank you.

138
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,422
Your legs don't hurt, do they?

139
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:27,882
Here you go, sir.

140
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:29,217
Oh, thanks.

141
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:31,594
Wow, what muscles.

142
00:08:31,719 --> 00:08:34,347
Wow! Wow! This is so great!

143
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:39,310
Four of the five strongest one-on-one
members of my research are here now!

144
00:08:39,393 --> 00:08:42,063
You sure look happy, Nirei-kun.
Good for you.

145
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:43,940
Aren't you happy, Sakura-kun?

146
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:45,566
You're among that five.

147
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:49,070
How strong is that guy?

148
00:08:49,153 --> 00:08:51,155
{\an8}Glad you asked!

149
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:55,409
<i>In middle school, he went to the famous
rich boy school Kanna Mid,</i>

150
00:08:55,493 --> 00:08:56,827
<i>but there are rumors that</i>

151
00:08:56,911 --> 00:08:59,997
<i>he beat up some third-years from
a famous delinquent school</i>

152
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,791
<i>all by himself in his first year!</i>

153
00:09:01,874 --> 00:09:03,084
What else?

154
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,920
You're really enthusiastic today, huh,
Sakura-san?

155
00:09:06,921 --> 00:09:10,716
Hurry! What else do you know about him?

156
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,094
Why are you so red?

157
00:09:13,177 --> 00:09:14,971
Don't worry about me! Tell me more!

158
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:18,474
-Look at this funny menu!
-He seems to be popular among girls.

159
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:22,353
She's wearing Seikai Girls' High uniform.
Maybe she's his girlfriend?

160
00:09:22,436 --> 00:09:23,813
That's not what I'm asking!

161
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:27,567
Sakura-kun is desperate
to not think about their relationship.

162
00:09:28,317 --> 00:09:32,113
What's the matter, Sakura-kun?
You're curious about Kiryu-kun?

163
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:35,616
Then we really should
all chat together. Kiryu-kun!

164
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:38,202
-Hey, stop it.
-Come over here and chat with us!

165
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:39,537
You too, missy!

166
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:41,372
Hey! I didn't ask you to do that!

167
00:09:41,455 --> 00:09:44,333
Sakura-kun said he's curious about you!

168
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:54,427
Oh, so your name is Sakura-chan.

169
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:57,680
Sorry, I do remember your face,
but not your name...

170
00:09:57,763 --> 00:09:59,557
You fought with Sugi-chan, right?

171
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:03,352
Yup! You're curious about
Sakura-kun too, right?

172
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:09,025
But I'm a bit busy at the moment,
so let's chat at school later.

173
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:10,359
Have you decided?

174
00:10:11,694 --> 00:10:14,405
I feel like I was just publicly shamed.

175
00:10:14,488 --> 00:10:15,823
That's not true!

176
00:10:15,906 --> 00:10:18,701
People can be curious
about various things!

177
00:10:18,784 --> 00:10:21,329
-Come on, don't be so cold, man!
-Wait, Tsugeura-san!

178
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:24,081
You haven't told me
your virtue yet, either!

179
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:25,958
Let's all have a fun chat together!

180
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:27,209
Yeah?

181
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:31,339
Sorry.

182
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:35,384
It's okay.
He's part of Furin, just like me.

183
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:38,179
But you must be so scared.

184
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:43,184
Will you please stop?

185
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:46,687
Huh? Stop what?

186
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:48,230
Tsuga-chan.

187
00:10:48,314 --> 00:10:49,565
It's Tsugeura.

188
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:54,278
Tsuge-chan, have you ever thought about
how you come off to other people?

189
00:10:54,362 --> 00:10:57,114
Huh? How I come off? As myself, of course.

190
00:10:57,823 --> 00:11:01,327
You're tall, bulky, and look strong.

191
00:11:01,952 --> 00:11:04,330
Your look can be scary to some people.

192
00:11:04,413 --> 00:11:09,335
If someone like you starts shouting,
girls would get frightened.

193
00:11:11,379 --> 00:11:14,840
You won't be popular with girls
with that attitude.

194
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:18,511
Huh? This... is looking bad...

195
00:11:19,303 --> 00:11:20,638
I...

196
00:11:21,389 --> 00:11:24,308
I'm scaring you? Sorry about that!

197
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:26,477
<i>-So straightforward!
-So straightforward!</i>

198
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:30,773
It's a little loud in here.
Let's go somewhere else.

199
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:34,068
I'm really sorry!

200
00:11:34,151 --> 00:11:35,569
<i>What a tiny voice.</i>

201
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:45,996
Did it hit that hard when he said
you're not popular with girls?

202
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:46,997
Not that.

203
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:51,585
Needlessly scaring other people
goes against my virtue.

204
00:11:51,710 --> 00:11:54,296
<i>He's surprisingly sensitive, huh?</i>

205
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:57,007
We finally found you!

206
00:11:57,091 --> 00:11:58,342
Surround him, boys!

207
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:00,719
What now?

208
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:03,973
Wow, you're so annoyingly persistent.

209
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:07,476
How dare you do me like that earlier?

210
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:10,062
But it was you who started it.

211
00:12:10,146 --> 00:12:14,316
You're scaring this poor girl.
How are you going to make up for it?

212
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:17,653
Hey, hey!

213
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:20,030
What's all this?

214
00:12:20,990 --> 00:12:24,827
<i>I saw this guy trying to pick up
this poor girl when I was passing by...</i>

215
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:28,205
<i>So I knocked him out and ran off with her.</i>

216
00:12:29,331 --> 00:12:32,334
And to think he'd drag
this many guys just to find us...

217
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:34,211
What a persistent jerk.

218
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:37,047
So she wasn't his girlfriend, huh?

219
00:12:37,131 --> 00:12:38,340
Looks like it.

220
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:42,636
Kiryu-kun! You're so cool!

221
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:45,139
Oh, thanks?

222
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:49,310
That means your virtue is
"being emphatic to girls"!

223
00:12:49,393 --> 00:12:51,604
Yeah! Great! That's awesome!

224
00:12:51,687 --> 00:12:54,148
Sure, but this isn't the time for that.

225
00:12:54,231 --> 00:12:57,735
Hey, orange buzzcut! I've got
a bone to pick with that pinkhead!

226
00:12:57,818 --> 00:13:01,113
It's also classy how you don't
boast about it, either!

227
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:03,449
Hey! Are you listenin', punk?

228
00:13:03,532 --> 00:13:05,784
Tsuge-chan,
let's save that for later, okay?

229
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:08,662
I knew I wasn't wrong about you!

230
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:10,456
You little punk!

231
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:16,754
Good grief...

232
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:21,759
Surrounding a few with larger numbers.
Talk about being super lame.

233
00:13:21,842 --> 00:13:24,220
-You punk!
-What do you think you're doing?

234
00:13:24,303 --> 00:13:27,723
I hate guys like you.

235
00:13:27,806 --> 00:13:31,227
Sakura-san!
You don't have to stir them up like that.

236
00:13:32,978 --> 00:13:35,606
Nice one, Sakura-kun! Well said!

237
00:13:36,023 --> 00:13:38,484
That makes me feel a bit better.

238
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:40,945
Let's step back a bit, shall we?

239
00:13:41,695 --> 00:13:43,489
It'll be okay.

240
00:13:45,157 --> 00:13:47,910
Those three are super strong.

241
00:13:59,296 --> 00:14:03,217
Aren't you hurt, Sakura-kun?
Sure you don't wanna sit this one out?

242
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:05,427
Huh? What are you talkin' about?

243
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:08,597
Man, sorry to get you guys involved.

244
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:12,351
Hey, Furin! I don't give a crap about
you being the town's shield or whatever!

245
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:13,811
Don't get carried away!

246
00:14:13,894 --> 00:14:15,688
Tsk, what a bunch of scum.

247
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:18,566
Well, let's get this over with quickly.

248
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:19,525
Get 'em!

249
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:21,861
All right! Come at me!

250
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:28,450
What? Tsugeura-san?

251
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:30,911
You're just all talk, huh?

252
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:34,707
Jeez, he shouldn't be
worrying about other people.

253
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,667
Now die!

254
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:43,883
You know, I always
let my opponent strike me first.

255
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:48,012
So now it's my turn.

256
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:54,435
A German suplex?

257
00:14:54,518 --> 00:14:56,395
He's as flashy as always.

258
00:14:57,938 --> 00:15:00,691
Let the opponent show their stuff,
then show mine.

259
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:03,444
That's my virtue!

260
00:15:04,445 --> 00:15:06,864
He's definitely gonna die young.

261
00:15:12,661 --> 00:15:15,331
That was dangerous!
Why'd you throw him at me?

262
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:19,710
Sorry, I thought it'd be faster
to just send them your way.

263
00:15:22,796 --> 00:15:24,506
Huh? Are you screwin' with me?

264
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:26,383
All right! Give 'em to me!

265
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:38,187
Kiryu-san is making Sakura-san
and Tsugeura-san fight for him?

266
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,939
Is he having fun with this?

267
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:40,856
Nah.

268
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:45,569
Kiryu-kun, you don't have to
worry about us here.

269
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:47,446
I'm here, after all.

270
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,367
Got it.

271
00:15:51,742 --> 00:15:53,369
He...

272
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,580
Why are you just chilling?

273
00:15:57,039 --> 00:16:00,292
Well, can you blame me? I am chill.

274
00:16:07,549 --> 00:16:10,302
Suo-chan is good! Just like the rumors!

275
00:16:11,053 --> 00:16:15,057
<i>He was trying to keep people
from coming at them?</i>

276
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:17,476
Kiryu-san! Behind you!

277
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:18,811
Huh?

278
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:25,985
Oh, thanks, Sakura-chan.

279
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:28,612
Leave 'em...

280
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:31,115
Bring it on.

281
00:16:31,198 --> 00:16:33,117
Leave 'em all to me.

282
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,663
You're so nice, Sakura-chan!

283
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:39,999
I'm not doing it for you!

284
00:16:40,082 --> 00:16:42,042
It just works better for me that way!

285
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:44,253
Kiryu-kun! Pass them to me, too!

286
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:50,801
Man...

287
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:53,095
How should I describe this?

288
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:56,849
They overwhelmed them.

289
00:16:56,932 --> 00:16:59,685
Sheesh, they're so weak,
that barely felt like a fight.

290
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:03,647
We took care of them so quickly.
You two are amazing!

291
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:06,275
Sakura-kun, say our slogan!

292
00:17:06,358 --> 00:17:07,443
Slogan?

293
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:09,737
Bofurin's slogan!

294
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,947
I'll have you take the best part!

295
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:13,032
Huh?

296
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:16,702
Sakura-san's from outside,
so he probably doesn't know about it.

297
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:18,328
Oh, that's right!

298
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:20,372
All right, then you better memorize it!

299
00:17:22,916 --> 00:17:26,837
Anyone who causes pain,
who brings destruction,

300
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:29,214
who holds evil in their heart

301
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:33,719
will be purged by Bofurin
without exception!

302
00:17:34,219 --> 00:17:37,097
You didn't have to yell that loudly.

303
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:38,515
<i>Those words...</i>

304
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:41,101
<i>They said it back then, too.</i>

305
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:44,521
Well, there you have it.

306
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:51,153
If you've got power, you should
use it for something better next time.

307
00:17:51,779 --> 00:17:53,614
Okay, sir...

308
00:17:57,493 --> 00:18:00,079
Don't do anything bad again!

309
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:02,498
All right, it's finally over!

310
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:04,833
It's all right now.

311
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:08,337
Thank you so much!

312
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:11,423
Thank you... Thank you so much!

313
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:16,053
Take care now!

314
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:21,100
Still, although I know you're strong
from your fight with Sugi-chan...

315
00:18:21,642 --> 00:18:23,685
you're really impressive, Sakura-chan.

316
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:27,940
Yeah! No wonder
he's tryin' to make it to the top!

317
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:29,399
Oh, really?

318
00:18:29,483 --> 00:18:31,985
What? You weren't listening back then?

319
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:34,655
<i>Oh, I did remember it being
very loud and rowdy, but</i>

320
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:37,074
<i>I was just getting to
the good part of my game.</i>

321
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:38,992
Even so...

322
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:42,538
I'm glad to know about you
before we decide on a grade captain.

323
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:44,832
Grade captain?

324
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:47,835
More importantly,
tell me your contact info.

325
00:18:47,918 --> 00:18:50,420
-What?
-I wanna have it, too!

326
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:53,674
How do I do this?

327
00:18:54,258 --> 00:18:55,509
Here, give me.

328
00:18:55,592 --> 00:18:56,927
Why is your face red?

329
00:18:57,719 --> 00:19:00,264
Oh, you haven't downloaded any app?

330
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:02,099
Then I'll have your number...

331
00:19:03,016 --> 00:19:05,519
There's only one registered number...

332
00:19:05,602 --> 00:19:06,687
"Weather?"

333
00:19:08,105 --> 00:19:09,273
What?

334
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:14,361
Why are you laughing?

335
00:19:14,444 --> 00:19:17,489
I'll check with you for the weather
from now on.

336
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:28,584
Why are you staring at your
phone for? Playing a game?

337
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:30,669
Why did you sneak up on me?

338
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:33,630
Oh, sorry.
I wasn't trying to freak you out.

339
00:19:33,714 --> 00:19:37,217
Anyway, you should finish your breakfast,
or you're gonna be late.

340
00:19:37,301 --> 00:19:39,011
GROUP: 1
FRIENDS: 4

341
00:19:40,470 --> 00:19:41,597
Give it back.

342
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:43,265
I added myself, too!

343
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:45,392
Who asked you to do that?

344
00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:48,103
You got yourself
Kotoha-chan's contact info!

345
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:50,939
Sheesh...

346
00:19:52,065 --> 00:19:53,984
{\an8}FURIN
KIRYU: MORNIN'

347
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:55,444
{\an8}<i>Huh? Why?</i>

348
00:19:55,903 --> 00:19:59,948
We'll see each other at school,
so why say this through text?

349
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:01,700
AKIHIKO NIREI:
YOU WERE ALL SO COOL YESTERDAY!

350
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:07,206
{\an8}GRADE CAPTAIN

351
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:09,166
YOU GUYS WEREN'T IN CLASS TWO DAYS AGO

352
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:10,918
SO IT'LL PROBABLY BE TODAY

353
00:20:11,001 --> 00:20:12,711
WAIT, HOLD ON
WHAT'S A GRADE CAPT

354
00:20:12,794 --> 00:20:14,213
GOT IT!

355
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,184
Oh, Sakura-san!

356
00:20:28,143 --> 00:20:29,394
Good morning.

357
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:30,938
-Morning!
-Good morning!

358
00:20:31,021 --> 00:20:33,148
What on earth is a grade captain?

359
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:35,609
What? Why are you so angry?

360
00:20:35,692 --> 00:20:39,905
Besides, why do you keep messaging
the stuff we could just say here?

361
00:20:39,988 --> 00:20:42,532
Huh? But isn't it more convenient?

362
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:45,786
I saw the read receipt,
so I knew you saw it...

363
00:20:45,869 --> 00:20:48,038
But it is hard
when you're still new to it.

364
00:20:48,121 --> 00:20:50,290
But don't worry, Sakura-kun.

365
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:52,626
We'll be talking about that now.

366
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:57,381
They're the grade captain and
vice captains of Tamon Team second-years.

367
00:20:57,464 --> 00:20:59,174
Hey, eyes up, guys!

368
00:20:59,716 --> 00:21:02,886
<i>Those guys... They're from back then, right?</i>

369
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:06,974
Oh! Wow, wow! They're famous second-years!

370
00:21:07,057 --> 00:21:08,183
Enomoto-san!

371
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:10,227
Hey! Sit your butts down!

372
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:11,895
Kusumi-san...

373
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:13,230
and Kaji-san!

374
00:21:13,313 --> 00:21:15,732
To think I'd get to see them
up close like this!

375
00:21:15,816 --> 00:21:19,111
<i>What's with that guy?
He doesn't seem to be interested at all.</i>

376
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:23,073
We're gonna have you guys decide
on a grade captain.

377
00:21:23,156 --> 00:21:27,744
The grade captain is the head of the class
and the one responsible for their actions.

378
00:21:27,828 --> 00:21:31,206
Any problems that come from this class
will be his responsibility.

379
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,667
You guys can decide on who
however you like.

380
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:35,544
Just hurry and get this done with.

381
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:39,214
<i>That means the grade captain
is sort of like the top of the class.</i>

382
00:21:40,048 --> 00:21:42,301
<i>Like that guy.</i>

383
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:43,552
Excuse me.

384
00:21:43,635 --> 00:21:46,179
Oh, Suo, you wanna run
for the grade captain?

385
00:21:46,263 --> 00:21:49,850
<i>He doesn't look like he'd volunteer
for something like this.</i>

386
00:21:52,352 --> 00:21:54,604
I think Sakura-kun will be a good fit.

387
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:57,941
What?

388
00:23:31,409 --> 00:23:33,620
So you have a smartphone, Sakura-san.

389
00:23:33,703 --> 00:23:35,497
Of course! What do you take me for?

390
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:36,540
Sorry.

391
00:23:36,623 --> 00:23:37,624
Let me see.

392
00:23:37,707 --> 00:23:39,751
No pictures...

393
00:23:39,835 --> 00:23:42,170
Your apps are still
only the defaults ones.

394
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:45,674
And your contact list... "Weather"?

